<section id="command-difference">
<title>DIFFERENCE</title>
<indexterm><primary>DIFFERENCE</primary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>-</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>DIFFERENCE</command> <parameter>number1</parameter> <parameter>number2</parameter>
<parameter>number1</parameter> <command>-</command> <parameter>number2</parameter></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Outputs the difference of its inputs.
</para>
<para>
The minus sign (-) means infix difference in ambiguous contexts (when preceded by a complete expression), unless it is preceded by a space and followed by a non-space.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<programlisting><userinput>SHOW 3 - 2</userinput>
1</programlisting>

<programlisting><userinput>SHOW DIFFERENCE 3 2</userinput>
1</programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>

</section>
